### Description

There is no explicit programmatic/imperative way of registering to `ModelSignal` changes from the parent except using an `effect`. Use case examples: dynamically created components and testing.

This also means that replacing two-way binding (an input + output with `Change` suffix) with `ModelSignal` will cause a breaking change to anything that programmaticaly/imperatively subscribes to the old output. 


### Proposed solution

- warn users in documentation that replacing input + output combination with `ModelSignal` should be considered a breaking change
- add a method to `ComponentRef` (e.g. `registerListener`)

### Alternatives considered

Using an `effect` or an util like `toObservable`:

```ts
class ChildCmp {
  name = model('');
}

// parent

const child = viewChild(ChildCmp)

effect(() => {
  console.log(child().name())
});

// or
toObservable(child().name).subscribe(...);
```

The other way would be using `.subscribe()` method but it is deprecated.

In certain cases, the plugin option may be a string value, as shown in the example below:

```json
{
 "plugins": {
  "tailwindcss/nesting": "postcss-nesting"
  }
}
```

See: https://tailwindcss.com/docs/using-with-preprocessors#nesting

